hwFirewallMIB.name: hwFirewallMIB

revisions.description: Modify hwFwBasicEventTime attribute type from DateAndTime to SnmpAdminString, make it analyze OCTET type time string successfully

hwFirewallMIB.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwFirewallMIB.description: The MIB contains objects of firewall , referencing the draft-grall-firewall-mib-01.

SecurityEvent.name: SecurityEvent
SecurityEvent.description: This textual convention is used to describe various security-related events and statistics on a firewall. attack : A packet forwarding attack has been detected. atkTerm : An attack has terminated blklstAdd : A black list is added manually or dynamically. blklstDel : A black list is deleted manually or dynamically.

Services.name: Services
Services.description: This textual convention is used to describe various services that are monitored by the firewall. protoIcmp : identifies ICMP, Internet Control Message Protocol. protoTcp : identifies TCP, Transmission Control Protocol. protoUdp : identifies UDP, User Datagram Protocol. protoIp : identifies IP, Internet Protocol. protoSnmp : identifies SNMP, Simple Network Management Protocol.

ConnectionStat.name: ConnectionStat
ConnectionStat.description: This textual convention is used to describe various connections statistics. totalOpen : Total open connections since reboot. currentOpen : The number of connections currently open. currentHalfOpen : The number of connections currently half-open. remote : The number of connections synchronized from remote backup firewall. high : The highest number of connections in use at any one time since system startup.

ConnectionEvent.name: ConnectionEvent
ConnectionEvent.description: This textual convention is used to describe various events and statistics that are related to the connections that occur on a firewall. other : A generic connection event. accept : A connection has been acccepted. error : An error has occurred for a connection. drop : The connection has been dropped. close : A connection has been closed. timeout : A connection has been timed out. refused : A connection has been refused. reset : A connection has been reset. noResp : A connection has received no response.

Hardware.name: Hardware
Hardware.description: This textual convention is used to describe various hardware resouces that can be monitored by the firewall. memory : identifies memory. disk : identifies disk. power : identifies power. netInterface : identifies a network interface. tape : identifies a tape drive. controller : identifies hardware controller. cpu : identifies CPU. primaryUnit : identifies the primary unit of the two identical firewalls configured redundancy. secondaryUnit : identifies the secondary unit of the two identical firewalls configured redundancy. other : identifies other hardware.

HardwareStatus.name: HardwareStatus
HardwareStatus.description: This textual convention is used to describe various events that are related to the resources on a firewall. other : Generic resource event. up : The resource is in service. down : The resource is not in service. error : There has been an error for this resource. overTemp : The resource is overheating. busy : The resource is busy. noMedia : A device doesn't have its needed media. backup : Processing has switched to the backup. active : This is the active unit. standby : This is the standby unit.

ResourceStatistics.name: ResourceStatistics
ResourceStatistics.description: This textual convention is used to identify various statistics that are related to the resources on a firewall. highUse : The highest load the resource has had for a time period. The time period will be implementation dependent. highLoad : The highest load the resource has had since startup. maximum : The maximum amount of the resource that is available. minimum : The minimum amount of the resource that is available. low : The lowest amount of the resource that has been available since startup. high : The highest amount of the resource that has been available since startup. average : The average amount of the resource that has been available since startup. free : The amount of the resource that is currently available since startup. inUse : The amount of the resource that is currently in use, eg. CPU usage, memory usage.

ContentInspectionEvent.name: ContentInspectionEvent
ContentInspectionEvent.description: Content inspection events, these events report that something was found in the application payload. The details entry in the event can report on what was found (eg., virus, company private info., etc), what it was found in (eg., html, win32 executable, e-mail), and what was done with it (eg., the quarantine location). other : A content inspection event. Used to indicate that some content inspection has occurred that is not covered by the other content inspection enumerations. okay : The check of the content was okay, nothing 'bad' was found. error : There was an error while checking the content. found : Something was found that the content inspection engine has determined merits attention. clean : The content inspection engine has found something that violates the security policy and has neutralized the content in the data flow. reject : The content inspection engine has found something that violates the security policy and has discarded the content. saved : The content inspection engine has found something that violates the security policy and has stored it in a quarentine storage area.

AccessEvent.name: AccessEvent
AccessEvent.description: This textual convention is used to describe various events and statistics that are related to the access control on a firewall. other : Miscellaneous access event. grant : A service has allowed access based on all of its access checks. deny : a client was denied use of a service. denyMult : A client was denied use of a service multiple times. error : An error has ocurred during the access control process.

AuthenticationEvent.name: AuthenticationEvent
AuthenticationEvent.description: This textual convention is used to describe various events and statistics that are related to authorization. other : Miscellaneous authentication event. succ : A client successfuly authenticated. error : Error while authenticating. fail : A client failed an authenticating. succPriv : A client accessed a service with special privileges. failPriv : A client failed to access a service with special privileges. failMult : Multiple failed authentication attempts by a client.

GenericEvent.name: GenericEvent
GenericEvent.description: Generic Events : events for which there is no more specific enumeration abnormal : An abnormal event has occurred that is neither 'okay' nor an 'error'. okay : A normal event occurred or the system has changed from an abnormal state to a normal state error : An error event occurred

PktFltDefaultRule.name: PktFltDefaultRule
PktFltDefaultRule.description: Default rule of the packet filtering. permit : Allows all packets to pass. deny : Rejects all packets.

AspfProto.name: AspfProto
AspfProto.description: Protocol enabled ASPF check function in interzone.

hwFwNetEventsTableLastRow.name: hwFwNetEventsTableLastRow
hwFwNetEventsTableLastRow.description: The index value of the last row in the hwFwNetEventsTable. This number starts at 1 and increase by one with each new log entry. When this number wraps, all events are deleted.

hwFwBasicEventsTableLastRow.name: hwFwBasicEventsTableLastRow
hwFwBasicEventsTableLastRow.description: The index value of the most recently created row in the cfwBasicEventsTable. This number starts at 1 and increase by one with each new log entry. When this number wraps, all events are deleted.

hwFwBasicEventsTable.name: hwFwBasicEventsTable
hwFwBasicEventsTable.description: Table of basic data for firewall events. The agent may choose to delete the instances of cfwBasicEventsEntry as required because of lack of memory. The oldest Events will be selected first for deletion.

hwFwBasicEventsEntry.name: hwFwBasicEventsEntry
hwFwBasicEventsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing general information about an event. This table will always be sparse, i.e., each row will instanciate only a subet of the columnar objects.

hwFwBasicEventIndex.name: hwFwBasicEventIndex
hwFwBasicEventIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the log table. These indices are assigned beginning with 1 and increase by one with each new event logged.

hwFwBasicEventTime.name: hwFwBasicEventTime
hwFwBasicEventTime.description: The time that the event occurred.

hwFwBasicSecurityEventType.name: hwFwBasicSecurityEventType
hwFwBasicSecurityEventType.description: The type of security-related event that this row contains. If the event is not security-related this object will not be instantiated.

hwFwBasicEventDescription.name: hwFwBasicEventDescription
hwFwBasicEventDescription.description: A description of the event. The value of the object may be a zero-length string.

hwFwBasicEventDetailsTableRow.name: hwFwBasicEventDetailsTableRow
hwFwBasicEventDetailsTableRow.description: A pointer to a row in the table containing details about this event. Generally, the table will be the cfwNetEventsTable but a Cisco-defined table may also appear here. If there there is no more detailed information for this event the value of this object will have the value {0 0}.

hwFwNetEventsTable.name: hwFwNetEventsTable
hwFwNetEventsTable.description: Table of detailed data for network events. The agent may choose to delete the instances of hwFwBasicEventsEntry as required because of lack of memory. It is an implementation-specific matter as to when this deletion may occur. It is recommended that the oldest log instances are deleted first.

hwFwNetEventsEntry.name: hwFwNetEventsEntry
hwFwNetEventsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing detailed information about an event. Note that this table may be sparse. If Network Address Translation is not enabled hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpAddress and hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpAddress will not be instantiated in the row. If Port Address Translation is not enabled hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpPort and hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpPort will not be instantiated in the row. Entries are added to this table at the same time that events are added to the hwFwBasicEventsTable. These two tables may be configured to be different sizes so there may not be a one-to-one correspondence between rows in the two tables.

hwFwNetEventIndex.name: hwFwNetEventIndex
hwFwNetEventIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies an entry in the log table. These indices are assigned beginning with one and increase by one with each new log entry. When this number wraps, all events are deleted in order to allow the NMS to differentiate between old and new events.

hwFwNetEventInterface.name: hwFwNetEventInterface
hwFwNetEventInterface.description: The interface most closely associated with this event. For example, for an event that relates to the receipt of a packet, this object identifies the interface on which the packet was received. If there are multiple interfaces associated with an event, the interface most closely associated with the cause of the event will be used. For example, for an event for the setup of a TCP connection, the interface on the initiator's side of the connection would be preferred. If there is no associated interface, then this object has the value zero.

hwFwNetEventSrcVrfName.name: hwFwNetEventSrcVrfName
hwFwNetEventSrcVrfName.description: This object indicates the VRF's name.

hwFwNetEventSrcIpAddress.name: hwFwNetEventSrcIpAddress
hwFwNetEventSrcIpAddress.description: Source IP address in the IP packet that caused the event. If there is no packet associated with the event this object has the value of zero. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different source addresses, this value may be zero or an address taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpAddress.name: hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpAddress
hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpAddress.description: Source IP address after Network Address Translation has been applied. If NAT has not been applied to the source address in this packet this object will not be instantiated, resulting in a sparse table. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different source addresses, this value may be zero or an address taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventDstVrfName.name: hwFwNetEventDstVrfName
hwFwNetEventDstVrfName.description: This object indicates the VRF's name.

hwFwNetEventDstIpAddress.name: hwFwNetEventDstIpAddress
hwFwNetEventDstIpAddress.description: Destination IP address in the IP packet that caused the event. If there is no packet associated with the event this object has the value of zero. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different destination addresses, this value may be zero or an address taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpAddress.name: hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpAddress
hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpAddress.description: Destination IP address after Network Address Translation has been applied. If NAT has not been applied to the destination address in this packet this object will not be instantiated, resulting in a sparse table. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different destination addresses, this value may be zero or an address taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventSrcIpPort.name: hwFwNetEventSrcIpPort
hwFwNetEventSrcIpPort.description: Source UDP/TCP port in the IP packet that caused the event. If there is no packet associated with the event this object has the value of zero. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different source ports, this value may be zero or a port taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpPort.name: hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpPort
hwFwNetEventInsideSrcIpPort.description: Source UDP/TCP port after Port Address Translation has been applied. If PAT has not been applied to the source port in this packet this object will not be instantiated, resulting in a sparse table. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different source ports, this value may be zero or a port taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventDstIpPort.name: hwFwNetEventDstIpPort
hwFwNetEventDstIpPort.description: Destination UDP/TCP port in the IP packet that caused the event. If there is no packet associated with the event this object has the value of zero. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different destination ports, this value may be zero or a port taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpPort.name: hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpPort
hwFwNetEventInsideDstIpPort.description: Destination UDP/TCP port after Port Address Translation has been applied. If PAT has not been applied to the Destination port in this packet this object will not be instantiated, resulting in a sparse table. If the event is the result of multiple packets with different destination ports, this value may be zero or a port taken from an arbitrarily chosen packet in the sequence of packets causing the event.

hwFwNetEventService.name: hwFwNetEventService
hwFwNetEventService.description: The identification of the type of service involved with this event.

hwFwNetEventServiceInformation.name: hwFwNetEventServiceInformation
hwFwNetEventServiceInformation.description: Specific service information. This can be used to describe the particular service indentified by hwFwNetEventService and can reflect whether the service is a local service or a gateway service. For example, if the value for hwFwNetEventService is loginTelnet then the string provided might be 'local telnet'.

hwFwNetEventIdentity.name: hwFwNetEventIdentity
hwFwNetEventIdentity.description: This object will contain a description of the entity that caused the event. The entity could be a userid, username, processid or other identifier for the entity using the service. If there is no such information then this object will contain a zero-length string.

hwFwNetEventDescription.name: hwFwNetEventDescription
hwFwNetEventDescription.description: A detailed description of the event.

hwFwConnectionStatEntry.name: hwFwConnectionStatEntry
hwFwConnectionStatEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a firewall statistic.

hwFwConnectionStatService.name: hwFwConnectionStatService
hwFwConnectionStatService.description: The identification of the type of connection providing statistics.

hwFwConnectionStatType.name: hwFwConnectionStatType
hwFwConnectionStatType.description: The state of the connections that this row contains statistics for.

hwFwConnectionStatDescription.name: hwFwConnectionStatDescription
hwFwConnectionStatDescription.description: A detailed textual description of this statistic.

hwFwConnectionStatCount.name: hwFwConnectionStatCount
hwFwConnectionStatCount.description: This is an integer that contains the value of the resource statistic. If a type of 'gauge' is more appropriate this object will be omitted resulting in a sparse table.

hwFwZoneNumOfEntries.name: hwFwZoneNumOfEntries
hwFwZoneNumOfEntries.description: This object maintains a count of the number of entries that currently exist in the hwFwZoneTable.

hwFwZoneEntry.name: hwFwZoneEntry
hwFwZoneEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a firewall zone.

hwFwZoneIndex.name: hwFwZoneIndex
hwFwZoneIndex.description: This object represents the name of a firewall zone.

hwFwZoneName.name: hwFwZoneName
hwFwZoneName.description: This object represents the name of a firewall zone.

hwFwZonePriority.name: hwFwZonePriority
hwFwZonePriority.description: This object represents the priority of a firewall zone.

hwFwZoneIfList.name: hwFwZoneIfList
hwFwZoneIfList.description: The set of interface which belong to the firewall zone.

hwFwZoneIfNum.name: hwFwZoneIfNum
hwFwZoneIfNum.description: The number of interface in this firewall zone.

hwFwInterZoneNumOfEntries.name: hwFwInterZoneNumOfEntries
hwFwInterZoneNumOfEntries.description: This object maintains a count of the number of entries that currently exist in the hwFwInterZoneTable.

hwFwInterZoneEntry.name: hwFwInterZoneEntry
hwFwInterZoneEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about a firewall Interzone.

hwFwInterZoneName.name: hwFwInterZoneName
hwFwInterZoneName.description: This object represents the name of a firewall Interzone.

hwFwInterZoneEnable.name: hwFwInterZoneEnable
hwFwInterZoneEnable.description: Enable or disable firewall on interzone, and show firewall status on interzone.

hwFwInterZonePktFltInDefaultRule.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltInDefaultRule
hwFwInterZonePktFltInDefaultRule.description: Default rule of the packet filtering that the direction is inbound.

hwFwInterZonePktFltInAcl.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltInAcl
hwFwInterZonePktFltInAcl.description: Basic or advanced acl number of the packet filtering that the direction is inbound.

hwFwInterZonePktFltInMacAcl.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltInMacAcl
hwFwInterZonePktFltInMacAcl.description: Layer 2 acl number of the packet filtering that the direction is inbound.

hwFwInterZonePktFltOutDefaultRule.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltOutDefaultRule
hwFwInterZonePktFltOutDefaultRule.description: Default rule of the packet filtering that the direction is outbound.

hwFwInterZonePktFltOutAcl.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltOutAcl
hwFwInterZonePktFltOutAcl.description: Basic or advanced acl number of the packet filtering that the direction is outbound.

hwFwInterZonePktFltOutMacAcl.name: hwFwInterZonePktFltOutMacAcl
hwFwInterZonePktFltOutMacAcl.description: Layer 2 acl number of the packet filtering that the direction is outbound.

hwFwInterZoneAspf.name: hwFwInterZoneAspf
hwFwInterZoneAspf.description: Type of protocol enabled aspf in this Interzone.

hwFwInterZoneSessLogInAcl.name: hwFwInterZoneSessLogInAcl
hwFwInterZoneSessLogInAcl.description: Acl number of interzone session log for inbound.

hwFwInterZoneSessLogOutAcl.name: hwFwInterZoneSessLogOutAcl
hwFwInterZoneSessLogOutAcl.description: Acl number of interzone session log for outbound.

hwFwSessionNatLogStatus.name: hwFwSessionNatLogStatus
hwFwSessionNatLogStatus.description: Whether session nat log is enabled.

hwFwSessionOutBandLogStatus.name: hwFwSessionOutBandLogStatus
hwFwSessionOutBandLogStatus.description: Whether the out-of-band mode of sending log is enabled.

hwFwBinaryLogSrcAddr.name: hwFwBinaryLogSrcAddr
hwFwBinaryLogSrcAddr.description: IP address used by the device to communicate with the log server.

hwFwBinaryLogSrcPort.name: hwFwBinaryLogSrcPort
hwFwBinaryLogSrcPort.description: Port number used by the device to communicate with the log server.

hwFwSipMediaAgingTime.name: hwFwSipMediaAgingTime
hwFwSipMediaAgingTime.description: Aging time for Sip media stream.

hwFwRtspMediaAgingTime.name: hwFwRtspMediaAgingTime
hwFwRtspMediaAgingTime.description: Aging time for Rtsp media stream.

hwFwSecurityNotification.name: hwFwSecurityNotification
hwFwSecurityNotification.description: This notification is used for events involving security events. The included objects provide more detailed information about the event.

hwFwInterzoneStatusNotification.name: hwFwInterzoneStatusNotification
hwFwInterzoneStatusNotification.description: This notification is used for events involving security events. Send out firewall enable or disable event in Interzone.

hwFirewallMIBCompliance.name: hwFirewallMIBCompliance
hwFirewallMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the hwFirewallMIB.

hwFirewallMIBZoneGroup.name: hwFirewallMIBZoneGroup
hwFirewallMIBZoneGroup.description: This is the firewall zone group.

hwFirewallMIBInterZoneGroup.name: hwFirewallMIBInterZoneGroup
hwFirewallMIBInterZoneGroup.description: This is the firewall interzone group.

hwFirewallMIBLogGroup.name: hwFirewallMIBLogGroup
hwFirewallMIBLogGroup.description: This is the firewall log group.

hwFirewallMIBAgingTimeGroup.name: hwFirewallMIBAgingTimeGroup
hwFirewallMIBAgingTimeGroup.description: This is the firewall Aging time group.
